The paper deals with game theoretic models and protocols for leader election in distributed systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of game theory and coalition formation suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Game Theory (cs.GT). The study of protocols and algorithms for distributed systems involves the use of data structures and algorithms, which falls under the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The focus on asynchronous rings and networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
